      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm struggling with a shopify theme. on mobile the product image is totally overlapping the title and description, it looks like a mess. i checked the css but cant see why it's happening on small screens. \n\nhere is the snippet i'm working with:\n\n.product-single__media {\n  float: left;\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\n.product-single__info {\n  float: right;\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\nany idea why this is breaking on mobile?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the classic case of the \"floating\" conundrum! The issue here is that your product images and titles are taking up the entire width of the screen, causing them to overlap on mobile devices. It's a common problem when using floats and fixed widths. \n\nTo fix this, you could try using media queries to adjust the widths and float properties for smaller screens. For example, you could set the product image and title to take up less space on mobile devices. Here's a modified snippet:\n\n```css\n.product-single__media {\n  float: left;\n  width: 30%;\n}\n\n.product-single__info {\n  float: right;\n  width: 70%;\n}\n\n@media (max-width: 768px) {\n  .product-single__media {\n    width: 100%;\n    float: none;\n  }\n\n  .product-single__info {\n    width: 100%;\n    float: none;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis should help prevent the overlapping issue on mobile devices. Remember, sometimes you need to adjust your layout for different screen sizes, and that's where media queries come in handy. Happy coding!",
      "source": "target",
