    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the notorious layout instability! It sounds like your elements are experiencing a bit of a \"jitterbug\" problem. This can happen when the browser is trying to recalculate the layout of your page after a change, like a refresh. It's like a group of unruly little gremlins causing a ruckus in your layout.\n\nTo help stabilize the layout, you can try adding some CSS transitions to your elements. This will smooth out the movement and make it less jarring for the user. Here's an example:\n\n```css\n.product-single__media,\n.product-single__info {\n  transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out;\n}\n```\n\nThis will add a gentle easing effect to the layout changes, reducing the \"jumpiness\" you see when the page refreshes. Give it a try and see if it helps with the stability issue. Happy coding!",
